Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Section 1: Recapitulation of sixPlaneAlpha", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"fe5a7c5b-6a40-4743-8c84-ffb3ab8ae148"],

Cell["\<\
The ambient space is R^8 endowed with the SO(4,4)-invariant split-signature \
metric:

  eta = diag(1,1,1,1,-1,-1,-1,-1),  i.e.  <x,x> = x0^2+x1^2+x2^2+x3^2 - \
x4^2-x5^2-x6^2-x7^2.

This is the standard pseudo-Euclidean norm on R^{4,4} studied in the \
repository.

The 16-component Dirac spinor Psi = {Psi1, Psi2} is decomposed under the 8x8 \
chirality operator sigma8 = Q[1].Q[2].Q[3]:
  * Psi1 (Type 1, left-handed): sigma8 . Psi1 = +Psi1
  * Psi2 (Type 2, right-handed): sigma8 . Psi2 = -Psi2

Via Cartan's triality (which identifies the vector, Type-1 spinor, and Type-2 \
spinor representations of Spin(4,4)), each 8-component chiral spinor maps to \
a vector in V = R^8:
  v1 = triality(Psi1),  v2 = triality(Psi2).

Two 7-planes (hyperplanes) are defined as the orthogonal complements to these \
vectors with respect to eta:
  H1 = { x in V : <x, v1>_eta = 0 }   (dimension 7)
  H2 = { x in V : <x, v2>_eta = 0 }   (dimension 7)

The intersection sixPlaneAlpha = H1 intersect H2 generically has dimension 8 \
- 2 = 6.

From the README: 'the 6-plane of their intersection identified; todo: \
associate 6-plane with 3 generations of Einstein-Rosen 2-planes.'

The key: 6 = 3 x 2, so sixPlaneAlpha decomposes into 3 real 2-planes, each \
one an Einstein-Rosen bridge generation.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f5158353-6731-46a4-8dae-ea3e9bdc800e"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Section 2: Explicit Construction of sixPlaneAlpha", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"5353d73a-d27f-4362-855e-d3c774399998"],

Cell["\<\
We work with the ambient R^8 and split metric eta = \
diag(1,1,1,1,-1,-1,-1,-1). The two 7-planes are defined by linear conditions \
on x: eta.v1 and eta.v2 are the normal covectors. sixPlaneAlpha = NullSpace \
of the 2x8 matrix [eta.v1; eta.v2]^T.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0814d6ff-edb8-4705-9ed6-4380a273633b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
(* ---- Symbolic construction ---- *)

(* Split metric for R^{4,4} *)
eta = DiagonalMatrix[{1,1,1,1,-1,-1,-1,-1}];
Print[\"Ambient split metric eta:\"];
Print[MatrixForm[eta]];

(* Symbolic normal vectors v1, v2 in R^8 (image of chiral spinors under \
triality) *)
Clear[v1s,v1,v2s,v2]
v1s = Array[Subscript[v1,#]&, 8];
v2s = Array[Subscript[v2,#]&, 8];

(* The two 7-planes H1, H2 are defined by the vanishing of eta-inner products \
*)
(* H1 = {x : x.eta.v1 = 0},  H2 = {x : x.eta.v2 = 0} *)
(* Normal covectors in the dual space *)
n1 = eta . v1s;
n2 = eta . v2s;

(* sixPlaneAlpha = H1 intersect H2 = NullSpace of normalMatrix *)
normalMatrix = {n1, n2};
Print[\"Normal matrix (2x8) whose null space is sixPlaneAlpha:\"];
Print[MatrixForm[normalMatrix]];\
\>", "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.983564611909197*^9, 3.983564629742622*^9}, {
  3.983564693059713*^9, 3.9835647300403767`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[4]:=",ExpressionUUID->"7076df76-949b-41ec-8d2d-0e0ad38d7f03"],

